<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1437,425,1172]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,714,740]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Paterson" box="[324,502,713,740]" firstAuthor="Paterson" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref195005" refString="Paterson, G. L. J. (1985) The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology Series, 49 (1), 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1985">Paterson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
found 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1901" box="[581,712,714,740]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="concreta">
<emphasis box="[581,601,714,740]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[614,712,714,739]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">concreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be identical with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? (Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[940,1064,714,740]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis box="[940,1064,714,740]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O. irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in almost every aspect, ascribing no specific value to differences in the arrangement or number of arm spines. In view of this, Paterson proposed to demote this species to a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? (Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[589,715,786,812]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis box="[589,715,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O. irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, restricted to the East Atlantic. Nevertheless, he also noted that the distinct characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1901" box="[438,572,822,848]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="concreta">
<emphasis box="[438,572,822,848]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O. concreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were constant over a wide range of sizes and geographical areas. 
<bibRefCitation author="Martynov &amp; Litvinova" firstAuthor="Martynov" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" refId="ref189845" refString="Martynov, A. V. &amp; Litvinova, N. M. (2008) Deep-water Ophiuroidea of the northern Atlantic with descriptions of three new species and taxonomic remarks on certain genera and species. Marine Biology Research, 4, 76 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000701840066" type="book" year="2008">Martynov &amp; Litvinova (2008)</bibRefCitation>
disputed the subspecific division of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? (Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[784,908,858,884]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis box="[784,908,858,884]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O. irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to them, several subspecies should not live syntopically as in the case of 
<emphasis box="[568,713,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
O. i. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? (Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[623,713,894,919]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">irrorata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[767,920,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
O. i. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1901" box="[822,920,894,919]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="concreta">concreta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, both known from the Bay of Biscay. Another example of co-existence can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieg" box="[637,788,929,955]" firstAuthor="Grieg" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref183024" refString="Grieg, J. A. (1932) Echinodermata. Report of the scientific results of the Michael Sars North Atlantic deep sea expedition 1910, 3 (2), 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="1932">Grieg (1932)</bibRefCitation>
, who identified both forms in the material collected by 
<emphasis box="[151,302,965,992]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Michael Sars</emphasis>
at a station located north of the 
<collectingRegion box="[676,755,966,992]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Azores</collectingRegion>
(sta 88: 
<geoCoordinate box="[858,957,965,992]" degrees="45" direction="north" minutes="26" orientation="latitude" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" precision="925" value="45.433334">45°26’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[970,1076,965,992]" degrees="25" direction="west" minutes="45" orientation="longitude" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" precision="925" value="-25.75">25°45’W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[1089,1187,965,992]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.12" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="m" value="3.12">3,120 m</quantity>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Martynov &amp; Litvinova" firstAuthor="Martynov" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" refId="ref189845" refString="Martynov, A. V. &amp; Litvinova, N. M. (2008) Deep-water Ophiuroidea of the northern Atlantic with descriptions of three new species and taxonomic remarks on certain genera and species. Marine Biology Research, 4, 76 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000701840066" type="book" year="2008">Martynov &amp; Litvinova (2008)</bibRefCitation>
were unsure if they represented two separate species or rather a single polymorphic species. In view of this, we have opted for a more conservative approach and maintain the historical species 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1901" box="[1302,1436,1038,1064]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="concreta">
<emphasis box="[1302,1436,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O. concreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
separate from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? (Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[310,433,1074,1100]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis box="[310,433,1074,1100]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O. irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Presently, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1901" box="[564,696,1074,1100]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="concreta">
<emphasis box="[564,696,1074,1100]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">O. concreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known with certainty in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1038,1117,1074,1100]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Azores</collectingRegion>
only by historical records of 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler, R." box="[151,332,1109,1135]" journalOrPublisher="Expeditions Scientifiques du Travailleur et du Talisman" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="245 - 311" part="8" refId="ref185741" refString="Koehler, R. (1906 b) Ophiures. Expeditions Scientifiques du Travailleur et du Talisman, 8, 245 - 311." title="Ophiures" type="journal article" year="1906">Koehler (1906b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mortensen" authorityYear="1933" box="[345,449,1109,1135]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Talisman" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[345,449,1109,1135]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Talisman</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cruise) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Cherbonnier &amp; Sibuet" box="[590,916,1109,1135]" firstAuthor="Cherbonnier" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="1333 - 1394" refId="ref176043" refString="Cherbonnier, G. &amp; Sibuet, M. (1972) Resultats scientifiques de la campagne Noratlante: Asterides et Ophiurides. Bulletin du Museum National D'histoire Naturelle, 102 (76), 1333 - 1394." type="journal article" year="1972">Cherbonnier &amp; Sibuet (1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<emphasis box="[928,1049,1109,1135]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Noratlante</emphasis>
cruise). See below remarks under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? (Lyman" authorityYear="1878" box="[151,343,1145,1171]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis box="[151,343,1145,1171]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Ophiura irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
